Potential auth method mismatch bug for public clients. If `supported_methods` contains only unsupported auth methods (not in SUPPORTED_TOKEN_ENDPOINT_AUTH_METHODS), line 87 returns `"none"` as a fallback even though the server explicitly doesn't support it. This will cause OAuth flows to fail when the provider requires a method we don't support.

```python
if not supported_methods:
    return "none"
if "none" in supported_methods:
    return "none"
if "client_secret_post" in supported_methods:
    return "client_secret_post"
if "client_secret_basic" in supported_methods:
    return "client_secret_basic"
# Should raise an error here instead of returning an unsupported method
raise ValueError(f"Server doesn't support any of our token endpoint auth methods: {supported_methods}")
```
