When a user creates a new note while viewing page 2 or later, the note won't appear in the visible list. The `createNoteSuccess` listener calls `loadNotebooks()` which reloads the current page, but the newly created note will be on page 1 (newest first by default). This creates a confusing UX where the note opens in the side panel but isn't visible in the table.

**Fix:** Reset to page 1 before reloading:
```typescript
createNoteSuccess: ({ createdNote }) => {
    if (!createdNote) {
        return
    }
    posthog.capture(AccountsEvents.NoteCreated, { notebook_short_id: createdNote.short_id })
    actions.selectNotebook(createdNote.short_id, { autofocus: 'end' })
    actions.setPage(1)  // This will trigger loadNotebooks() via the setPage listener
},
```
